section.section:
Transportation offered by the Calvert County Board under this section shall be offered to a student attending a nonpublic school:
If there is sufficient capacity on the school bus;
If the student resides on, along, or near a public highway in the county on which a public school bus or conveyance operates;
If the student resides in the public school transportation district served by the public school bus;
Only on the routes, school days, and hours of transportation that coincide with the routes, school days, and hours of transportation for students attending public schools in the county; and
In the case of a student who attends a nonpublic school that is not on the public school bus route, only to the public school on the route which is nearest to the nonpublic school.
